headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 20 points and the Washington Wizards handed the slumping Charlotte Hornets their fifth straight loss, 108-100 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma, Wizards hand Hornets fifth straight loss, 108-100

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 34 points, K.J. Martin came off the bench to add 21 and the Houston Rockets snapped a six-game losing streak with a 134-127 win over the Orlando Magic on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets snap 6-game losing streak, beat Orlando 134-127

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 25 points, Cade Cunningham had 21 points and 11 rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 112-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey scores 25, Pistons' big 2nd half beats Thunder 112-103

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Myles Turner had season highs of 37 points and 12 rebounds, and the Indiana Pacers beat the New Orleans Pelicans 129-122 on Monday night for their fourth win in five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner has 37 points, 12 rebounds, Pacers beat Pelicans

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 33 points and 10 rebounds in his return after missing three games with the flu, Georges Niang scored 21 points on 7-for-10 shooting on 3-pointers, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Phoenix Suns 100-88 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has double-double in return, 76ers beat Suns 100-88

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 25 points, rookie A.J. Griffin came off the bench in Trae Young's absence to add a career-high 24 and the Atlanta Hawks snapped the Milwaukee Bucks’ season-opening, nine-game winning streak with a 117-98 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young sits, but Murray, Hawks hand Bucks 1st loss of season

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Portland didn't call time. Josh Hart called game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hart hits 3 at buzzer to give Blazers 110-107 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored a season-high 30 points and the Chicago Bulls coasted to a 111-97 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine's 30 points pace Bulls past Raptors 111-97

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 39 points, including a pair of free throws with 2.2 seconds left, and the Boston Celtics held on for a 109-106 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's 39 points help Celtics hold on to beat Grizzlies

events.name: New York Knicks at Minnesota Timberwolves
Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 26 points and 10 assists, Michael Porter Jr. added 24 points and the Denver Nuggets defeated the San Antonio Spurs 115-109 on Monday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic powers Nuggets past Spurs for 3rd straight victory

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 36 points, becoming only the second NBA player ever with nine consecutive games of at least 30 to begin the season, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Brooklyn Nets 96-94 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic extends 30-point streak to 9, Mavs edge Nets 96-94

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored a season-high 47 points, knocking down seven 3-pointers, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Sacramento Kings 116-113 on Monday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 47, Warriors beat Kings to end 5-game skid

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 23 points, Jordan Clarkson added 22 and the Utah Jazz beat Los Angeles 139-116 on Monday night, their second victory over the short-handed Lakers in four days.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz roll past Lakers again, 139-116 with LeBron sitting

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 26 points and made the tiebreaking three-point play with 37 seconds left, and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from a 13-point deficit in the final five minutes to snap the Cleveland Cavaliers' eight-game winning streak with a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally late, snap Cavaliers' 8-game win streak
